  13,29,"Those who believe and do good, for them will be bliss and an honourable destination.‚ÄĚ"
  13,30,"And so We have sent you ňĻO Prophetňļ to a community, like ňĻWe did withňļ earlier communities, so that you may recite to them what We have revealed to you. Yet they deny the Most Compassionate.¬†Say, ‚ÄúHe is my Lord! There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. In Him I put my trust, and to Him I turn ňĻin repentanceňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  13,31,"If there were a recitation that could cause mountains to move, or the earth to split, or the dead to speak, ňĻit would have been this Quranňļ. But all matters are by God‚Äôs Will. Have the believers not yet realized that had God willed, He could have guided all of humanity? And disasters will continue to afflict the disbelievers or strike close to their homes for their misdeeds, until God‚Äôs promise comes to pass. Surely God never fails in His promise"
  13,32,"Other messengers had already been ridiculed before you, but I delayed the disbelievers ňĻfor a whileňļ then seized them. And how ňĻhorribleňļ was My punishment"
  13,33,"Is ňĻthere any equal toňļ the Vigilant One Who knows what every soul commits? Yet the pagans have associated others with God ňĻin worshipňļ. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúName them! Or do you ňĻmean toňļ inform Him of something He does not know on the earth? Or are these ňĻgodsňļ just empty words?‚ÄĚ In fact, the disbelievers‚Äô falsehood has been made so appealing to them that they have been turned away from the Path. And whoever God leaves to stray will be left with no guide"
  13,34,"For them is punishment in this worldly life, but the punishment of the Hereafter is truly far worse. And none can shield them from God"